  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Personal Assistant to Director",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Provide full administrative support to the management team</li>\n  <li>Handle day-to-day administrative duties and documentation</li>\n  <li>Support the Directors in daily operations and project coordination</li>\n  <li>Manage calendars, scheduling meetings and sending reminders</li>\n  <li>Coordinate closely between office and project site supervisors to ensure smooth workflow and communication</li>\n  <li>Follow up on material deliveries, equipment requests and manpower deployment</li>\n  <li>Communication effectively with Project site supervisors to ensure clear understanding of project instructions and updates</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Proficient in MS Office (Outlook, Teams, Excel, Word, PowerPoint)</li>\n  <li>Basic understanding of landscape workflow and project site operations is an advantage</li>\n  <li>Good communication skills (able to liaise with Indian supervisors and site teams)</li>\n  <li>Excellent interpersonal skills and the ability to work effectively as part of the team</li>\n  <li>Strong coordination and time management skills to prioritize tasks under pressure</li>\n  <li>Highly organized, detail-oriented</li>\n  <li>Discretion and confidentiality when handling sensitive information</li>\n</ul>",
